name: David's Favorite Football Dip
author: Anna Schultz
summary: I created this recipe and it was instantly my husband's favorite football season dip!
ingredients: salt and ground black pepper to taste
directions: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Cook and stir ground turkey in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; add onion and bell pepper
Cover skillet and simmer until onion is softened, about 5 more minutes
Transfer turkey mixture to a bowl
Stir baked beans, refried beans, and coconut oil together in the same skillet used for turkey mixture; cook and stir over medium heat until beans are heated through, 5 to 7 minutes
Mix salsa,  , ranch dressing, soy sauce, and liquid smoke into bean mixture and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and mozzarella cheese
Cover skillet and cook until cheeses melts, 3 to 5 minutes
Mix bean mixture into ground turkey mixture and stir well; season with salt and pepper
